# Keep tooling, docs, and credentials OUT of the public deployment.
# .vercelignore excludes files from the Vercel upload, so nothing here is ever
# served at a public URL. It does NOT affect the Git repo or GitHub Actions.

# GitHub-only tooling (workflows + the maintainer credentials note)
.github/

# Project docs — reference material, not site content
BLOG-SETUP.md
CONTRIBUTING.md
DEPLOY.md

# Local env scaffolding (also gitignored, listed here as belt-and-suspenders)
.env
.env.local
.env.example

# Python build caches
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
